blog.name: hallowgrove
blog.title: Hallow Grove
blog.description:
Welcome to Hallow Grove, Louisiana.

Whether you’ve been here your whole life, or are coming for the first time, there’s just something about Hallow Grove, LA that just feels like home. A surprising little town with a rich history and more to offer than you could ever imagine, its no wonder you would ever want to leave. So whether you’re just passing through, or setting down roots we’d love to have you here in Hallow Grove.

Hallow Grove is a mature original character roleplay, based in a small town just outside of New Orleans.

Mobile Navigation

summary: All things Mira LeRoux... Age: 30 years old Occupation: Photographer, Videographer, & Waitress at Grace’s Diner Birthdate: 1st...
caption:
All things Mira LeRoux…

Age: 30 years old
Occupation: Photographer, Videographer, & Waitress at Grace’s Diner
Birthdate: 1st of October 1988
Sexuality: Bisexual
Gender: Female
Neighborhood: Marseille
How long they’ve lived in Hallow Grove: April of 2017
Faceclaim: Brie Larson 

History

Mira grew up in a household of four, two parents and one brother. As a family they lived in Berkeley, California, overlooking the San Francisco Bay. Though, her father was absent most of the time due to being a film producer. Most of his works were popular in the industry. This inspired the young girl to create her own ‘home’ movies. Owning her first vintage handheld camcorder is where her collection all started. By the age of 22, the female owned various vintage camcorders and cameras. Photography becoming a great love as well.

Filmmaking wasn’t the best idea for her, or at least, that is what her father expected. Even denying that Mira should go to New York Film Academy. So, instead, the female traveled several hours away to take classes at UCLA. Living in Los Angeles was an eye-opening experience for the brunette. While attending the university, she took a bike delivery job. Mira loved every waking moment of it, especially all the scars and bruises that came with it. Several years passed, as well as some hard breakups, eventually leaving the female guarded when it came to relationships. It wasn’t long after graduation the female decided to leave and travel the states. Even earning a job with National Geographic as a photographer and videographer. During the time, Mira had the mistake of a one night stand and became pregnant.

Deciding to keep the child had been the best decision ever. The duration of each term was spent traveling until coming close to her due date. Settling down in a small city called Eze on the coast of France, there her son Dexter was born. Mira stayed there until Dex reached just about a year old before traveling around Europe some more. When the boy was eventually old enough to attend a school, they traveled back to Eze. Dexter turned out to be a very smart boy, picking up French just as fast as he picked up English. They stayed in the small city until Dexter reached the age of six before making the decision to move elsewhere. It was Dex, her son who picked their next destination to live. Choosing Louisiana surprised her, but the girl couldn’t object.

When choosing a place in Louisiana to live Mira wanted a town not too small and not too big that was how she found Hallow Grove. It was located close to New Orleans, a perfect place for her to do her photography work and the new place to explore with her son, Dexter. Every day was a journey for them and being back in the states after almost eight years made her anxious. But was Mira was determined to get through whatever life brought their way.

Hallow Grove turned out to be a staple in her life. There she meets more than one person, who now she considers as family. Above it all, there was Jack. The only father figure Dexter ever had. Mira was grateful when the older man opened his home to the young mom and her son. For once in her life, she didn’t feel like running away. The years living in Hallow Grove only seemed to get better. Dexter was happy, which only fueled her happiness. With having Jack there in between, it all added a little something extra for the both of them. Her heart was growing for the older man, and she hoped one day that he would see it too. Not only just for her but for her son as well.
